rComments: A kind and responsive professor, but no PPTs, have to just listen to him speaking for 1.5hr without subtitles so far. Sometimes it's really difficult to understand the word he just said.

This professor is amazing! He listened to our concerns and compromised with us when we brought up issues. The evaluations seem intimidating at first, but if you took good notes, you will do great! 3 open-book midterms and 1 open-book reflection. I could not have asked for a better prof for this course!

Prof is very organized, and cares that his students understand the content. When there were problems with the transition to online school, the prof listened to students' concerns and tried his best to fix it. The lectures are very thorough, and easy to follow, but you need good notes for the exams. Plan to take the whole allotted time!
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Amazing lectures ', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: Wasnt looking forward to taking this course, but was surprisingly interesting. Course material was abstract, and there were a lot of readings, but the quizzes/final were all easy to follow. Prof was available to answer questions 24/7, and took time to ask for student feedback, and was willing to modify evaluations/teaching methods if requested!

Pretty decent overall! Made easy-to-understand lectures, even though online learning is awkward for everyone and the content itself was very heavy. Enjoyed hearing about Szasz from him. He marked easy, but not necessarily fairly: about 60% of the grade was crammed into the last week or so. Would probably take again.

Originally, the class and its content appeared very intimidating but it ended up being very easy if you can memorize the content from class and do a few select readings before the tests. Very easy marker and really wants his class to succeed. Overall, very kind professor - Highly recommend!
